    "summary": "Mark Lindenberg is a visual/cultural anthropologist and documentary filmmaker. He received his BA in Cinematography in 2013 from Film academy Amsterdam. In 2021 he also received an MSc with cum laude honour in Cultural Anthropology and Development Sociology with the specialisation Visual Ethnography at Leiden. He combined his two studies to conduct multispecies ethnography research in the Peruvian Amazon region on how plants and humans relate, communicate and cooperate during healing endeavours. Other topics of interest are medical anthropology, shamanism, witchcraft, healing, spirituality and psychedelic anthropology. His work has been awarded amongst others by the Society of Visual Anthropology winning the Graduate Student Award for Outstanding Work, the EASA2022 conference winning the Mantas Kvedaravi\u010dius film award and the AVA 2021 Award for Best Visual Ethnographic Material Addressing Ageing and the Life Course. Next to the academic recognition his films have been awarded and shown on venues across the earth. \n\nMSc Cultural Anthropology and Development Sociology - Leiden University\nBA Cinematography - Amsterdam University of the Arts",
